<section xml:id="section-assignment2">
  <title>Assignment 2</title>
  <p><ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Describe these lines as offset spans. Everything is in
        <m>\RR^3</m>. (6)
        <ol>
          <li>
            The line through <m>(0,3,2)</m> with direction
            <m>(-4,-4,1)</m>.
          </li>
          <li>
            The line perpendicular to the plane <m>5x - y + 3z = 0</m>
              and through the point <m>(-2,2,-7)</m>.
          </li>
          <li>
            The line which is the intersection of th planes <m>-4x +
            5y - z = 0</m> and <m>3x - y + z = 0</m>.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Find equations for these planes. (9)
        <ol>
          <li>
            The plane parallel to <m>x - y - z = 0</m> but three units
            away in the positive <m>z</m> direction.
          </li>
          <li>
            The plane with normal <m>(-1,-5,3)</m> through the point
            <m>(2,2,2)</m>.
          </li>
          <li>
            The plane through the points <m>(-1,1,0)</m>,
            <m>(-2,-2,1)</m> and <m>(3,4,-4)</m>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Two planes <m>P_1</m> and <m>P_2</m> have normals <m>n_2</m>
        and <m>n_2</m>. What can you say about <m>n_1 \times
        n_2</m>? (4)  
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Prove the following statments for vectors in <m>\RR^3</m>.
        (18) 
        <ol>
          <li>
            <me>
              u \times (v + w) = (u \times v) + (u \times w) 
            </me>
          </li>
          <li>
            <me>
              u \times (v \times w) = (u \cdot w) v - (u \cdot v) w
            </me>
          </li>
          <li>
            <me>
              u \times (v \times w) + v \times (w \times u) + w \times
              (u \times v) = 0
            </me>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        How does the matrix 
        <me>
          M = \begin{pmatrix} 
            0 \amp 3 \amp -1 \\
            -2 \amp 1 \amp 1 \\
            -1 \amp 0 \amp 3
          \end{pmatrix}
        </me>
        act on the following vectors. 
        <md>
          <mrow>
            a) \amp v = \begin{pmatrix}
              0 \\
              0 \\
              -5
            \end{pmatrix} 
            \amp b) \amp v = \begin{pmatrix}
              -1 \\
              -1 \\
              -1
            \end{pmatrix} 
            \amp c) \amp v = \begin{pmatrix}
              7 \\
              -12 \\
              4
            \end{pmatrix} 
            \amp d) \amp v = \begin{pmatrix}
              \dfrac{1}{5} \\
              \dfrac{-3}{24} \\
              \dfrac{-4}{5} 
            \end{pmatrix} 
          </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Calculate the detemrinants of these matrices. (12) 
        <md>
          <mrow>
            a) \amp \begin{vmatrix}
              0 \amp -4 \amp 1 \\
              3 \amp -2 \amp -8 \\
              0 \amp 1 \amp 6
            \end{vmatrix}
            \amp b) \amp \begin{vmatrix}
              0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 4 \\
              -1 \amp -8 \amp 2 \amp 1 \\
              0 \amp 2 \amp 3 \amp 0 \\            
              -1 \amp -3 \amp -2 \amp 5 
            \end{vmatrix}
            \amp c) \amp \begin{vmatrix}
              \dfrac{1}{5} \amp \dfrac{2}{7} \amp 0 \\
              \dfrac{-2}{3} \amp \dfrac{-2}{5} \amp \dfrac{1}{3} \\
              \dfrac{-3}{4} \amp \dfrac{1}{4} \amp 0              
            \end{vmatrix}
          </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol></p>
</section>
